result.execSummary:
The defendant Vincent J. Gomez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 3rd Degree Sexual Assault, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: The defendant shall pay Department of Correction fees as directed by the agent.

miscConds.notes: Victim has 30 days to request restitution on case 14CM70 which dismissed and read-in to this case.

Costs to be paid on a schedule established by the agent.  Defendant is ordered to pay the $250.00 DNA surcharge, provide a sample for testing through the Dept. of Corrections as required in felony/sexual assualt convictions.

Defendant shall attend counseling/programing as deemed appropriate by the agent releasing all records to the agent upon request.
Defendant is required to register/report as a sex offender.

The defendant shall have no contact with C.M. of any kind, whether direct or indirect, including in person, in writing, by phone, by e-mail or other electronic means, through a third party or in any other way.
Defendant is not to have any unsupervised contact with anyone age 17 years or younger with the exception of incidental contact in public areas.

timeConds.notes: Defendant granted credit for 116 days served and huber priveleges.

superMiscConds.notes: Fine and/or costs to be paid on a schedule established by the agent.  Defendant is ordered to pay the DNA surcharge, and to make arrangements to provide a DNA sample for testing through the Clark County Sheriff Department or if on probation, to the Department of Corrections as is required in all criminal convictions.

The defendant shall pay Department of Correction fees as directed by the agent.  The defendant shall submit to random urine/PBT testing as required by the agent or any law enforcement officer.
Defendant is to register with the Sex Offender Registry (SORP) Defendant is to comply with Sex Offender Rules of Supervision and rules of Community Supervision.

The defendant shall have no contact with Cheyanne Moen of any kind, whether direct or indirect, including in person, in writing, by phone, by e-mail or other electronic means, through a third party or in any other way.
Defendant is not to have any unsupervised contact with anyone age 17 years or younger with the exception of incidental contact in public areas.
Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcohol, and not go into places that sell alcohol except incidentally such as a grocery store, convenience store or gas station or other such place where alcohol is not sold for consumption on the premises.
Defendant is not to possess any illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia. Additionally, defendant may possess prescription drugs only when prescribed by a medical professional for the defendant, which shall be taken as prescribed.

Defendant shall attend counseling, treatments, programming, evaluations as deemed appropriate by the agent releasing all records to the agent upon request  The counseling is to include Sex Offender Counseling
